text.tspan: Prevalence of depression by age, World
Share of individuals within a given age category with depressive disorders. This is measured across both sexes.
Figures attempt to provide a true estimate (going beyond reported diagnosis) of depression prevalence based on
medical, epidemiological data, surveys and meta-regression modelling.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
